    <div class="text-block">
        <p>Based on discussions with the client, we came to conclusion that the primary user for this feature within the system would be <strong>Bob, a tier 3 service manager</strong>. In short his role is to keep the service department active with consistent business. This can anything from doing routine oil changes to performing diagnostic services. The overarching goal of the distributed marketing platform would be to assist Bob in keeping his department flowing with business. This led to a couple considerations:
            <ul>
                <li>How do I make a non-marketer (Bob) become a proficient marketer?</li>
                <li>How do I streamline this process so it does not interfere with Bob’s day-to-day operations? I wanted Bob to spend no more than 20 minutes within this feature</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>To address these considerations we set out to understand the goals for Bob. The goals I saw fit for Bob were as follows:
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Set expectations</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>How long will it take (for direct mail)?</li>
                        <li>What do most people do?</li>
                        <li>What's most successful? ROI?</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Exploration</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Marketing categories in human terms</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Consider Audience</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Limitations for data present? Does he need to concern himself what percentage of his target audience has both email and an address on file.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </div> 

